export let flowersData = [ { "rose" :
    `Roses, celebrated globally for their exquisite beauty and fragrance, require specific care to flourish spectacularly each season. The optimal time to plant new roses is during the dormant season, typically in late autumn or early spring, as this reduces transplant shock and allows roots to establish before summer heat. For the best growth, roses thrive in rich, well-draining soil with a slightly acidic pH, and they demand at least six hours of direct sunlight daily. Pruning is a crucial annual task best performed in early spring as the buds begin to swell, which encourages vigorous new growth and abundant blooms. The proper technique involves making clean, angled cuts above an outward-facing bud, removing dead or diseased wood entirely and selectively trimming healthy canes to maintain an open, balanced shape. Feeding roses adequately is vital; use a balanced granular or slow-release fertilizer monthly from early spring through mid-to-late summer to supply necessary nutrients. Supplement this with organic matter, like compost or well-rotted manure, applied as a mulch around the base of the plant. Adhering to these seasonal cycles of planting, pruning, and feeding ensures a healthy, vibrant rose garden.`
},
{"sunflowers": `Ornamental sunflowers need many hours of bright sunlight every day.
They grow very well when the sun shines on them for six hours or more.
The best soil for these flowers is loose and lets water drain away easily.
You should not let the soil stay too wet because the roots might rot.
It is a good idea to dig the soil before planting to make it soft.
You can plant the seeds in the garden when the spring weather gets warm.
Make sure there is no more cold frost before you put seeds in the ground.
Put each seed about two centimeters deep into the soft earth.
Leave a lot of space between the plants so they can grow big.
You can plant them directly in the garden to save time and effort.
Give the small plants a little bit of water every morning.
Tall sunflowers do not need water every day unless the weather is very hot.
Always put the water on the ground instead of on the leaves.
Keeping the leaves dry helps the plant stay healthy and look good.
Sunflowers need good food from the soil to make big, colorful flowers.
Using old compost from your garden is a great way to feed them naturally.
You can add a little liquid fertilizer every two weeks for better results.
Stop giving them extra food once you see the flowers starting to open.
If the sunflowers grow very tall, they might need a stick for support.
Use a soft string to tie the plant to the stick so it does not fall.
Look at the leaves often to make sure no bugs are eating them.
Cutting the flowers for a vase will make your house look very bright.
Change the water in the vase every day to keep the flowers fresh.
Leaving the flowers in the garden is good for the bees and the birds.`},
{"lavender": `Lavender loves to grow in very sunny spots with plenty of fresh air.
It needs at least six to eight hours of direct sunlight every day.
The best soil for lavender is sandy and contains many small stones.
This plant does not like to sit in soil that stays wet or heavy.
It prefers soil that lets water flow away very quickly and easily.
You should plant lavender in the spring when the ground starts to warm up.
Make sure to leave plenty of space between each plant for air to move.
Newly planted lavender needs a little water every few days to start growing.
Once the plant is established, it becomes very strong and needs little water.
Only water the lavender when the ground feels very dry to the touch.
Too much water can be bad for the roots and might make them rot.
You do not need to buy expensive fertilizers for this hardy plant.
Lavender actually grows better in poor soil than in very rich soil.
A tiny bit of compost in the spring is enough to keep it happy.
Adding a little bit of lime to the soil can help the plant grow better.
You should prune the plant once the flowers have finished blooming.
Cutting the green stems helps the lavender stay in a nice, round shape.
Be careful not to cut into the old, woody parts of the plant.
You can harvest the flowers just as they begin to open in the summer.
Tie the flowers in small bunches and hang them to dry in the shade.
The dried flowers will keep their lovely scent for a very long time.
Bees and butterflies will enjoy visiting your lavender all summer long.
It is a very easy plant to care for if it has enough sun and dry feet.
Growing lavender is a simple way to make your garden smell wonderful.`},
{"orchids": `Orchids are a diverse and fascinating family of flowering plants that require specific care to thrive. They typically prefer bright, indirect light, as direct sunlight can scorch their leaves. The ideal temperature for most orchids is between 60-80°F (15-27°C), with a slight drop at night to mimic their natural environment. Orchids need well-draining soil, often a special orchid mix that includes bark, perlite, and sphagnum moss to ensure proper aeration and moisture retention. Watering should be done carefully; it's best to water orchids once a week, allowing the potting medium to dry out slightly between waterings. Overwatering can lead to root rot, so it's crucial to ensure that the plant is not sitting in water. Fertilizing orchids every two weeks during the growing season with a balanced orchid fertilizer can promote healthy growth and blooming. Additionally, orchids benefit from high humidity levels, which can be achieved by placing a humidity tray nearby or using a room humidifier. With proper care, orchids can produce stunning blooms that last for several weeks, making them a cherished addition to any plant collection.`},
{"daisies": `Daisies are cheerful and easy-to-grow flowers that can brighten up any garden. They thrive best in full sun, needing at least six hours of direct sunlight each day to produce abundant blooms. The ideal soil for daisies is well-draining and moderately fertile, with a slightly acidic to neutral pH. To plant daisies, choose a location with good air circulation and space them about 12-18 inches apart to allow for growth. Water the plants regularly, especially during dry spells, but be careful not to overwater as daisies do not like soggy soil. Mulching around the base of the plants can help retain moisture and suppress weeds. Deadheading spent flowers encourages continuous blooming throughout the growing season. Daisies are relatively low-maintenance and can tolerate a range of conditions, making them a popular choice for both beginner and experienced gardeners alike.`},
{"peonies": `Peonies are beloved for their large, fragrant blooms and lush foliage, making them a standout in any garden. They prefer full sun to partial shade, with at least six hours of direct sunlight daily for optimal flowering. The best soil for peonies is rich, well-draining, and slightly acidic to neutral in pH. When planting peonies, it's important to choose a location with good air circulation to prevent fungal diseases. Plant the peony roots with the eyes (buds) no more than 2 inches below the soil surface to encourage blooming. Water the plants deeply and regularly during the growing season, especially during dry periods, but avoid overwatering as peonies do not like soggy soil. Mulching around the base can help retain moisture and suppress weeds. Peonies benefit from a balanced fertilizer applied in early spring and again after blooming. With proper care, peonies can thrive for decades, producing stunning blooms year after year.`},
{"tulips": `Tulips are vibrant and popular spring-blooming flowers that require specific care to flourish. They thrive best in full sun, needing at least six hours of direct sunlight each day for optimal growth and blooming. The ideal soil for tulips is well-draining and moderately fertile, with a slightly acidic to neutral pH. To plant tulip bulbs, choose a location with good air circulation and space them about 4-6 inches apart, planting the bulbs at a depth of 6-8 inches. Water the bulbs thoroughly after planting to help them establish roots, but be careful not to overwater as tulips do not like soggy soil. Mulching around the planting area can help retain moisture and suppress weeds. After blooming, allow the foliage to die back naturally, as this helps the bulbs store energy for the next growing season. With proper care, tulips can provide a stunning display of color each spring.`},
{"lilies": `Lilies are elegant and fragrant flowers that require specific care to thrive. They prefer full sun to partial shade, with at least six hours of direct sunlight daily for optimal growth and blooming. The ideal soil for lilies is well-draining and rich in organic matter, with a slightly acidic to neutral pH. When planting lily bulbs, choose a location with good air circulation and space them about 8-12 inches apart, planting the bulbs at a depth of 6-8 inches. Water the bulbs thoroughly after planting to help them establish roots, but be careful not to overwater as lilies do not like soggy soil. Mulching around the base can help retain moisture and suppress weeds. Lilies benefit from a balanced fertilizer applied in early spring and again after blooming. With proper care, lilies can provide stunning blooms year after year.`},
{"marigolds": `Marigolds are vibrant and easy-to-grow flowers that can add a splash of color to any garden. They thrive best in full sun, needing at least six hours of direct sunlight each day for optimal growth and blooming. The ideal soil for marigolds is well-draining and moderately fertile, with a slightly acidic to neutral pH. To plant marigold seeds, choose a location with good air circulation and space them about 8-12 inches apart to allow for growth. Water the plants regularly, especially during dry spells, but be careful not to overwater as marigolds do not like soggy soil. Mulching around the base of the plants can help retain moisture and suppress weeds. Deadheading spent flowers encourages continuous blooming throughout the growing season. Marigolds are relatively low-maintenance and can tolerate a range of conditions, making them a popular choice for both beginner and experienced gardeners alike.`},
{"hydrangeas": `Hydrangeas grow very well in places with mild summers and cool winters.
They are very popular in gardens across Europe, Asia, and North America.
The best time to plant these shrubs is during the spring or the autumn.
You should avoid planting them during the hottest part of the summer.
These plants love soil that is rich in nutrients and stays a little moist.
The ground must be able to drain water easily so the roots stay healthy.
Hydrangeas like a spot with bright morning sun and some afternoon shade.
The large leaves can wilt quickly if the afternoon sun is too hot.
You can actually change the flower color by changing the acidity of the soil.
Acidic soil usually makes blue flowers while alkaline soil makes them pink.
It is a good idea to feed the plants in early spring before they grow.
A balanced fertilizer or organic compost works very well for their growth.
You can apply a little more food in the middle of the summer season.
Do not give them fertilizer in late autumn because they need to rest.
Water the plants at the base to keep the flowers and leaves dry.
Adding a layer of mulch around the plant helps the soil stay cool.
Hydrangeas produce beautiful, large clusters of flowers for many weeks.
They are easy to care for and make any garden look very elegant.`},
{"irises": `Irises are very strong plants that can survive cold winter weather.

They grow best in places with plenty of sunlight and a bit of wind.

You can find these beautiful flowers in gardens all around the world.

The best time to plant iris rhizomes is in late summer or early fall.

They need a sunny spot where the sun shines for at least six hours.

Irises love soil that is loose and lets water drain away very fast.

If the soil is too wet, the thick roots can rot and die.

Make sure to plant the rhizome so the top is still visible above the dirt.

They do not like to be buried deep under the heavy ground.

You should feed your irises in the early spring when they start growing.

Use a fertilizer that is low in nitrogen to help the flowers grow.

It is also helpful to feed them again after the flowers have finished.

Avoid putting fertilizer directly on the thick roots of the plant.

Water them regularly when they are new, but do not overwater them later.

Give them more water during the hot and dry days of summer.

Irises look like colorful butterflies resting on top of tall green stems.

They are very easy to grow and return to the garden every single year.

You can divide the plants every few years to make your garden bigger.`},
{"cherry": `Cherry blossom trees grow best in places with four distinct seasons.

They need a cool winter to rest before they bloom in the spring.

These trees are very famous in Japan and the United States.

Many people travel to see them bloom in big parks and cities.

You should plant a cherry blossom tree in the late autumn or early spring.

The tree should be planted while it is sleeping and has no leaves.

They love soil that is rich and lets water flow through easily.

The ground should not stay too wet because the roots need air.

Pick a spot in your garden that gets plenty of bright sunlight.

Sunlight helps the tree produce many beautiful pink or white flowers.

You should feed the tree once a year in the early spring.

Use a balanced fertilizer before the small flower buds start to open.

Do not give the tree too much food because it can hurt the roots.

Young trees need plenty of water to help them grow strong.

Once the tree is older, it can handle dry weather much better.

Always water the base of the tree instead of the branches.

Pruning the tree in the summer helps it stay healthy and beautiful.

These trees grow quite large, so give them a lot of space in the garden.

The flowers only last for a few weeks before they fall like snow.

Watching the petals fall is a very peaceful and lovely experience.

They are a sign that the warm spring weather has finally arrived.

A healthy tree can live for many decades in a good spot.`},
{"gardenias": `Gardenias love warm weather and plenty of moisture in the air.

They grow very well in warm places like the southern United States and Asia.

The best time to plant them is in the spring or during the mild fall.

These plants need special soil that is acidic and rich in organic matter.

The ground should stay moist but must also let extra water drain away.

Gardenias like a spot with bright light and some shade from the hot sun.

You should feed your gardenias in the early spring and again in the summer.

Use a fertilizer that is specifically made for plants that love acidic soil.

Do not give them any more food once the autumn weather starts to get cold.

Water the plants regularly so the soil never becomes completely dry.

Always pour the water on the ground to keep the white flowers from turning brown.

If the leaves look yellow, the plant might need a little extra iron.

The flowers have a very strong and sweet scent that smells wonderful.

Pruning the bushes after they finish blooming helps them stay neat and healthy.

They need to be protected from freezing temperatures and strong, cold winds.

With the right food and warm sun, gardenias will bloom for a long time. They are a beautiful addition to any garden and can also be grown in pots indoors.`},
{"chrysanthemums": `Chrysanthemums grow very well in sunny places with plenty of fresh air.

They are very popular in China and Japan and have been grown there for centuries.

You can find these colorful flowers in many gardens during the autumn season.

The best time to plant them is in the spring so they have time to grow strong roots.

Many people also plant them in late summer to enjoy their flowers right away.

They love soil that is very rich and full of good nutrients from compost.

The ground must let water pass through easily so the roots do not stay too wet.

Mums need at least six hours of bright sunlight every day to bloom properly.

If the plants stay in the shade, they will not produce many flowers.

Water the plants regularly to keep the soil damp but never soaked or muddy.

It is better to water the base of the plant to keep the leaves dry and healthy.

You should feed them with a balanced fertilizer starting in the early spring.

Give them a little more food every month until the summer season ends.

Stop using fertilizer once the small flower buds start to appear on the stems.

Pinching the tops of the green stems in early summer makes the plant more bushy.

This simple trick helps the plant grow more flowers instead of just growing tall.

Chrysanthemums come in many beautiful colors like yellow, red, white, and purple.

They are very tough plants and can handle the first light frost of the winter.

You can cut the flowers to make a beautiful and bright bouquet for your home.

The flowers stay fresh for a very long time after you put them in a vase.

In very cold places, you should cover the ground with mulch to protect the roots.

This keeps the plant safe from freezing when the winter temperatures drop.

They are a famous symbol of the autumn season and bring joy to any garden.

Healthy chrysanthemums will return every year if you take good care of them.`},
{"carnations": `Carnations grow best in places with cool summers and bright sunlight.

They are grown all over the world, especially in countries like Colombia and Spain.

You should plant them in the spring after the cold frost has passed.

These flowers love a sunny spot where they can get plenty of light.

The best soil for carnations is sandy and allows water to drain quickly.

They prefer soil that is slightly alkaline rather than acidic.

Do not let the ground stay too wet, as this can hurt the roots.

You should feed the plants once a month during the spring and summer.

Use a balanced liquid fertilizer to help them grow big, healthy blooms.

Stop giving them food once the winter weather starts to arrive.

Water the plants at the base to keep the leaves and flowers dry.

Putting water on the leaves can cause spots or diseases to grow.

You can pick off the dead flowers to help the plant grow new ones.

If the stems get too long, they might need a small stick for support.

Carnations have a very sweet and spicy scent that many people love.

The flowers come in many colors like red, pink, white, and yellow.

They are very popular for bouquets because they stay fresh for a long time.

These plants are quite tough and can survive for several years in a garden.

Make sure to leave enough space between plants so the air can move around.

Fresh air helps keep the plants healthy and free from bugs.`},
{"dahlias": `Dahlias love warm weather and lots of bright sunshine every day.
They cannot survive cold frost, so they need protection in the winter.
These flowers are very popular in Mexico, Europe, and the United States.
You should plant dahlia tubers in the late spring when the soil is warm.
Make sure the danger of frost is completely gone before you start planting.
They prefer soil that is very rich in nutrients and drains water well.
The ground should be soft and loose so the roots can grow easily.
You can add some compost to the soil to help the plants grow strong.
It is important to pick a sunny spot that is protected from strong winds.
Start feeding your dahlias about one month after you plant them.
Use a fertilizer that is low in nitrogen to get more beautiful flowers.
You should feed the plants every three or four weeks during the summer.
Stop giving them food in late summer so the tubers can prepare for winter.
Water the plants deeply twice a week if the weather is very dry.
Always water the base of the plant and try to keep the leaves dry.`},
{"poppies": `Poppies are beautiful flowers that grow very well in cool and temperate climates.
They are famous for growing in many places like Europe, Asia, and North America.
You can find them growing wild in fields or in many home gardens.
The best time to plant poppy seeds is in the early spring or late autumn.
These seeds need a period of cold weather to help them wake up and grow.
They love soil that is very loose and lets water drain away quickly.
Poppies do not like to grow in heavy clay or very wet ground.
You should pick a spot in your garden that gets plenty of bright sunlight.
Most poppies do not like to be moved, so it is best to plant seeds directly in the ground.
These plants are very tough and do not need a lot of extra fertilizer.
You can add a little bit of organic compost to the soil before you plant the seeds.
If you want more flowers, you can use a balanced fertilizer once in the spring.
Do not give them too much food because it can make the stems too weak.
Water the plants regularly when they are young to help them get started.
Once they are older, poppies can handle dry weather and do not need much water.
The flowers only last for a short time, but they look very bright and colorful.`},
{"bluebells": `Bluebells are lovely flowers that grow best in cool and shady places.
They are very famous in the United Kingdom and across many parts of Europe.
You often see them growing in large groups under the shade of big trees.
The best time to plant bluebell bulbs is in the middle of autumn.
Planting them before the winter allows the roots to grow strong in the cold.
They love soil that is rich in old leaves and organic matter.
The ground should stay moist but it must also drain water well.
They do not like soil that is very dry or too hard.
You should pick a spot in the garden that gets partial shade or filtered light.
These flowers do not need a lot of extra food to grow well.
You can add a little bit of leaf compost to the soil in the spring.
A simple balanced fertilizer can be used once when the green leaves appear.
Stop feeding the plants once the flowers start to fade away.
Water them gently if the spring weather is very dry and hot.
Bluebells will spread naturally and create a beautiful blue carpet every year. They are a wonderful sight in the spring and can live for many years in the same spot.`},
{"camellias": `Camellias are beautiful evergreen shrubs that love mild and humid climates.
They are very popular in gardens across Asia, the United Kingdom, and the southern United States.
The best time to plant camellias is in the autumn or the early spring.
You should avoid planting them during the hottest months of the summer.
These plants need acidic soil that is rich in organic material like compost.
The ground must be able to drain water very well to keep the roots healthy.
Camellias prefer a spot with partial shade where they are protected from the hot afternoon sun.
They also like a quiet place that is shielded from strong and cold winds.
You should feed your camellias in the spring after the flowers have finished blooming.
Use a special fertilizer made for acid-loving plants to help them grow.
You can feed them again in the middle of the summer for better health.
Do not give them any food in the autumn or winter when the plant is resting.
Water the plants regularly to keep the soil moist but never too wet.
Adding a layer of bark or leaves around the base helps the soil stay cool.
Camellias have shiny green leaves and produce stunning flowers in the winter or spring. They are a wonderful addition to any garden and can also be grown in pots indoors. With proper care, camellias can bloom for many years, providing beauty and color even in the colder months.`},
{"hibiscus": `Hibiscus plants grow best in warm climates with plenty of bright sunshine.
They are very common in tropical places like Hawaii, Asia, and Florida.
You can plant hibiscus in the garden during the warm days of spring.
Make sure the weather is not cold because they love the heat to grow well.
These plants prefer soil that is very rich and contains a lot of nutrients.
The ground must be loose so that extra water can flow away easily.
Hibiscus roots do not like to sit in water for a long time.
You should choose a sunny spot where the plant gets at least six hours of light.
Water the plant often to keep the soil moist, especially during the summer.
You should feed your hibiscus regularly during the spring and summer months.
Use a fertilizer that has a lot of potassium to help the flowers bloom.
It is best to give them food once every two weeks in the growing season.
Stop giving them fertilizer during the winter when the plant is resting.
Adding some organic compost to the dirt helps the plant stay healthy.
The large and colorful flowers make any garden look like a tropical paradise. They can also be grown in pots on a sunny balcony or patio. With proper care, hibiscus plants can bloom for many years, providing vibrant color and beauty to your outdoor space.`},
{"jasmine": `Jasmine plants grow best in warm climates with plenty of bright sunshine.
They are very popular in many tropical and subtropical parts of Asia.
Many people love to grow them near windows or porches for their scent.
You should plant jasmine in the spring or during the early autumn.
This gives the roots enough time to get strong before the weather changes.
These plants love soil that is rich and has plenty of organic matter.
The ground must be well-drained so the roots do not stay too wet.
Jasmine prefers a spot that gets full sun or at least a little shade.
Good airflow around the plant helps keep the leaves healthy and green.
You should water the jasmine regularly to keep the soil slightly moist.
During the hot summer months, the plant might need water every day.
Feed your jasmine with a balanced fertilizer during the growing season.
It is best to give them food once a month from spring to summer.
Stop giving them fertilizer in the winter when the plant grows slowly.
Adding a layer of mulch around the base helps keep moisture in the soil.
The beautiful white flowers have a very sweet and famous smell. They can be used to make perfumes or simply enjoyed in the garden. With proper care, jasmine plants can bloom for many years, filling the air with their delightful fragrance.`},
{"snapdragons": `Snapdragons grow very well in cool weather and can even handle a light frost.
They are popular in gardens across Europe, North America, and parts of Africa.
The best time to plant them is in the early spring or late autumn.
They love a sunny spot but appreciate some shade during very hot days.
The soil should be rich in nutrients and allow water to drain away easily.
These plants do not like to sit in heavy or very muddy ground.
You should plant the seeds or small plants about 20 centimeters apart.
Water them regularly at the base to keep the soil moist but not soaked.
Adding a little bit of compost to the dirt helps them grow much faster.
You should feed snapdragons with a balanced fertilizer every two weeks.
Start giving them food in the spring when they begin to grow taller.
Stop using fertilizer once the weather becomes very hot in the summer.
If you cut off the dead flowers, the plant will grow many new ones.
Tall snapdragons might need a small stick to help them stay upright.
The flowers come in many bright colors and look like little dragon faces. They are a cheerful addition to any garden and can bloom for a long time with proper care. Snapdragons are also great for cutting and making beautiful bouquets for your home.`},
{"lotus": `Lotus plants grow best in very warm climates with plenty of hot summer sun.
They are very famous in many parts of Asia, especially in India and China.
The best time to plant lotus is in late spring when the water is warm.
The water temperature should be at least 20 degrees for the plant to grow.
These plants need heavy clay soil or special pond mud to stay in place.
They do not like sandy soil because it is too loose for their roots.
You must plant them in a large container or at the bottom of a pond.
The container needs to be deep enough to hold both mud and still water.
Lotus plants need at least six hours of direct sunlight every single day.
You should feed them with special fertilizer tablets made for water plants.
Start giving them food once the first leaves are floating on the water.
It is best to feed them once a month during the hot summer season.
Stop giving them food in the autumn when the leaves start to turn brown.
Never drop fertilizer directly on the growing point of the young plant.
The flowers are very beautiful and represent peace in many different cultures. They can bloom for many years if they have the right warm water and food. With proper care, lotus plants can provide stunning blooms that last for several weeks, making them a cherished addition to any water garden or pond.`},
{"wisteria": `Wisteria plants grow best in places with full sun and temperate weather.
They are very common in gardens across China, Japan, and the United States.
You should plant wisteria in the spring or during the early autumn.
These climbing plants need a lot of space and a very strong support to grow.
They love soil that is deep, rich, and can drain water very quickly.
The ground should stay moist but it must not be too wet or muddy.
Pick a spot where the plant can get at least six hours of sunlight every day.
Sunlight is very important for the plant to produce many purple flowers.
You should feed wisteria in the early spring before the leaves appear.
Use a fertilizer that is low in nitrogen to help the flowers grow better.
If you use too much nitrogen, you will get many leaves but no flowers.
You can add some compost to the base of the plant once every year.
Water the plant regularly during the first year to help the roots grow.
Older wisteria plants can handle dry weather much better than young ones.
Pruning the long stems twice a year helps the plant stay healthy and neat.`},
{"anemones": `Anemones grow very well in cool and mild climates with plenty of fresh air.
They are very popular in many gardens across Europe, North America, and Asia.
The best time to plant anemone bulbs is in the autumn or early spring.
You should soak the hard bulbs in water for a few hours before planting.
These plants love soil that is loose and very rich in organic matter.
The ground must be able to drain water quickly so the bulbs do not rot.
They prefer a spot that gets bright morning sun and some afternoon shade.
In very hot places, they need protection from the strong midday heat.
You should add some compost to the soil before you start planting.
Feed the plants with a balanced fertilizer when the first leaves appear.
You can give them a little more food once every month during the spring.
Stop giving them fertilizer after the flowers have finished blooming.
Water the plants regularly to keep the soil moist but never too wet.
Adding a layer of mulch helps keep the ground cool and holds moisture.
These delicate flowers come in many colors like blue, white, and red.`},
{"foxgloves": `Foxgloves grow very well in cool and mild climates with plenty of moisture.
They are very popular in gardens across Europe and parts of North America.
You often find them growing in open woods or near the edge of a forest.
The best time to plant foxglove seeds is in the late spring or summer.
They often bloom in their second year because they take time to grow strong.
These plants love soil that is rich in organic matter and very moist.
The ground must drain water well so the roots stay healthy and firm.
They prefer a spot with partial shade but can grow in the sun if it is cool.
You should pick a place that is protected from very strong and dry winds.
Add some compost or old leaves to the soil before you start planting.
You can feed the plants with a balanced fertilizer in the early spring.
Give them a little more food when you see the tall flower spikes appear.
Do not give them too much fertilizer or the stems might grow too weak.
Water the plants regularly to keep the soil from becoming completely dry.
Be careful because all parts of the foxglove plant are poisonous if eaten.
These tall and beautiful flowers bring a lovely look to any shady garden.`},
{"cosmos": `Cosmos flowers grow very well in warm climates with lots of bright sunshine.
They are native to Mexico but people grow them in gardens all over the world.
The best time to plant cosmos seeds is in the spring after the frost is gone.
They love warm soil and will grow very quickly when the weather is hot.
These plants prefer soil that is not too rich or full of heavy nutrients.
They actually grow better in poor or average soil that drains water well.
If the soil is too rich, you will get many leaves but very few flowers.
You should pick a sunny spot where they can get at least six hours of light.
Cosmos plants do not need a lot of extra fertilizer to stay healthy.
In fact, you usually do not need to feed them at all during the season.
Too much food can make the stems grow too tall and fall over easily.
Water the young plants regularly until they are a few inches tall.
Once they are grown, cosmos can handle dry weather and do not need much water.
You can remove the old, dead flowers to help the plant grow new blooms.
These colorful flowers attract many beautiful butterflies and bees to your garden.`},
{"zinnias": `Zinnias grow very well in hot climates with plenty of bright sunshine.
They are originally from Mexico and are now popular in gardens everywhere.
You should plant zinnia seeds in the spring when the soil is warm.
Make sure there is no more cold frost before you put them in the ground.
These flowers love soil that is rich in nutrients and drains water well.
The ground should be loose so the roots can spread out very easily.
They prefer a spot in the garden that gets full sun all day long.
You should space the plants apart so that fresh air can move between them.
Good airflow helps to keep the leaves dry and prevents plant diseases.
Water the plants at the base and avoid getting the leaves wet.
You should feed your zinnias with a balanced fertilizer every few weeks.
Start giving them food in the early summer when they begin to bloom.
Adding a little compost to the soil before planting helps them grow strong.
If you pick the old flowers, the plant will grow many new ones quickly.
Zinnias come in many bright colors like red, orange, pink, and yellow.`},
{"sweet"/*sweet peas*/: `Sweet peas grow best in cool climates and do not like very hot weather.
They are very popular in gardens across the United Kingdom and North America.
You should plant the seeds in the early spring as soon as the soil can be worked.
In warmer places, people often plant them in the late autumn for winter flowers.
These climbing plants need a tall fence or a trellis to grow upward.
They love soil that is very rich, deep, and has plenty of organic matter.
The ground must be able to drain water well so the roots do not rot.
Before planting, you can add some old manure or compost to the soil.
Choose a sunny spot where the plants can get plenty of morning light.
It is helpful to soak the seeds in water for a few hours before planting them.
Water your sweet peas regularly to keep the soil consistently moist.
You should feed the plants with a high-potassium fertilizer every two weeks.
Start giving them food when the first flower buds begin to appear.
Removing the dead flowers every day helps the plant produce more blooms.
The flowers are famous for their beautiful colors and very sweet perfume.`},
{"bird-of-paradise": `The bird-of-paradise is a beautiful plant that grows best in warm and sunny climates.
It is native to South Africa but is very popular in places like California and Florida.
These plants cannot handle freezing weather and need protection from the cold.
The best time to plant them is in the spring or early summer when it is warm.
They love soil that is very rich in nutrients and holds some moisture.
The ground must also drain water well so the roots do not stay too wet.
You should pick a sunny spot in your garden where the plant can get lots of light.
In very hot areas, the plant might like a little bit of shade in the afternoon.
Water the plant regularly during the summer to keep the soil slightly moist.
During the winter, you should water them less because the plant grows slowly.
You should feed your bird-of-paradise every two weeks during the growing season.
A balanced fertilizer works well to help the plant stay strong and healthy.
Stop giving them food during the autumn and winter months when they rest.
Adding organic compost to the soil once a year helps the flowers bloom better.
The flowers look like the heads of colorful birds and stay beautiful for a long time. With proper care, bird-of-paradise plants can bloom for many years, providing a tropical feel to your garden.`},
{"begonias": `Begonias are very popular plants that grow best in warm and humid climates.
They are commonly grown in gardens and homes all over the world.
Most begonias do not like cold weather and cannot handle freezing frost.
The best time to plant them is in late spring when the air is warm.
They love a spot with partial shade where the sun is not too strong.
The soil should be very light, airy, and rich in organic material.
It is important that the ground drains water quickly to protect the roots.
You should keep the soil moist but be careful not to water them too much.
Begonias grow very well in garden beds, hanging baskets, and pots.
You should feed them with a balanced fertilizer once every month.
Start giving them food in the spring when you see new growth.
A liquid fertilizer works very well to keep the leaves green and healthy.
Stop feeding the plants in the autumn when the weather starts to get cool.
Always water the soil directly and try to keep the leaves dry.
These plants have beautiful flowers and leaves that come in many colors. They are a wonderful addition to any garden or indoor space and can bloom for many years with proper care.`},
{"forget-me-nots": `Forget-me-nots are lovely small flowers that grow best in cool and damp climates.
They are very popular in gardens across Europe, North America, and New Zealand.
The best time to plant the seeds is in the late summer or early autumn.
They often bloom in the following spring when the weather is still mild.
These plants love soil that is very rich and holds a lot of moisture.
The ground should stay damp but it must not be completely flooded.
They prefer a spot with partial shade or light sun throughout the day.
Forget-me-nots often grow naturally near streams or in shady woodland areas.
You should add some organic compost to the soil before you start planting.
You can feed them with a balanced fertilizer once in the early spring.
Usually, they do not need much extra food if the soil is already healthy.
Water the plants regularly to make sure the dirt never dries out completely.
These flowers are famous for spreading their own seeds around the garden.
This means they will often grow back every year without any extra work.
The tiny blue flowers with yellow centers look very beautiful in the spring.`},
{"pansies": `Pansies are very hardy plants that love cool weather and mild temperatures.
They can survive light frost and even small amounts of snow in the winter.
These flowers are very popular in gardens across Europe and North America.
The best time to plant pansies is in the early spring or the late autumn.
They grow best when the soil temperature is between 7 and 18 degrees.
Pansies love soil that is very rich, fertile, and holds moisture well.
The ground must drain water easily so the roots do not become soggy.
They prefer a sunny spot but appreciate some shade in warmer areas.
You should space the plants about 15 to 25 centimeters apart in the garden.
Water your pansies regularly to keep the soil consistently moist for growth.
You should feed them with a balanced liquid fertilizer every few weeks.
Start giving them food in the spring to help them produce many flowers.
Adding some organic compost to the soil helps the plants stay very healthy.
If you remove the old and dead flowers, the plant will bloom for longer.
These cheerful flowers come in many bright colors and have "faces" on them.`},
{"freesias": `Freesias are beautiful flowers known for their sweet and pleasant fragrance. They belong to the iris family and come from South Africa. These plants grow best in a mild Mediterranean climate with cool nights. They do not like very hot weather and cannot survive hard frost. Most freesias are grown in greenhouses in the Netherlands or in gardens in warm places like California. You should plant the bulbs in the fall if you live in a warm area. In colder places, it is better to plant them in the spring after the frost is gone. They need a sunny spot but also like some shade during the hottest part of the day. The best soil for freesias is light, sandy, and drains water very quickly. They do not like to stay in wet soil because the bulbs can rot. You should provide plenty of water while the plants are growing and blooming. When the first green shoots appear, you can start using a liquid fertilizer. It is good to feed them every two weeks until they finish flowering. High-potassium fertilizer helps them produce more colorful and healthy blooms. After the flowers fade, you should stop fertilizing and let the leaves dry out naturally. These flowers are very popular for bouquets because they stay fresh for a long time in a vase. Growing freesias is a rewarding hobby because they bring bright colors and a lovely scent to any home.`},
{"queen"/*queen anne's lace*/: `Queen Anne's Lace is a lovely wildflower that belongs to the carrot family. It is native to Europe and parts of Asia but now grows all over the world. This plant is very hardy and can tolerate many different types of climates. It grows best in temperate regions with full sun or very light shade. You can find it growing most often in open fields, along roadsides, and in meadows. Many people consider it a wild plant, but it is also grown in gardens for its delicate white flowers. If you want to plant it, you should sow the seeds in early spring or late autumn. It does not require special care because it is very adaptable to its environment. This plant prefers well-drained soil that is slightly dry rather than very wet. It can grow easily in poor, sandy, or rocky soil where other plants might struggle. Because it is a wild species, it generally does not need much extra fertilizer to grow well. If your soil is very poor, you can add a little bit of general-purpose fertilizer in the spring. Too much nitrogen will make the leaves grow large but will result in fewer flowers. You should water the young plants regularly until they become strong and established. Once they are mature, they are very drought-tolerant and can survive with very little water. Many gardeners love this plant because it attracts beneficial insects like butterflies and bees to the garden. The flowers are very small and white, arranged in a flat-topped cluster that looks like lace. It is a beautiful and delicate addition to any wildflower garden or naturalized area.`},
{"ranunculus": `Ranunculus flowers are famous for their many layers of delicate, paper-thin petals. They grow from small roots that look like tiny claws and produce very bright colors. These plants prefer a cool climate with mild winters and moderate spring temperatures. They do not grow well in very high heat or intense humidity during the summer. Ranunculus are most commonly grown in places like Italy, France, and parts of California. If you live in a warm area, you should plant the roots in the late autumn. In colder regions, it is best to plant them in early spring after the risk of hard frost. They need a location that gets full sun for at least six hours every day. The ideal soil for these flowers is rich, light, and must drain water very efficiently. They do not like sitting in soggy ground because the roots can easily rot. You should water them regularly when you see the first leaves appearing above the soil. It is helpful to use a balanced liquid fertilizer every two weeks during the growing season. Once the flower buds start to show, a fertilizer high in phosphorus will help them bloom. You should stop watering and feeding the plants once the foliage turns yellow and dies back. Many people grow them in pots or garden beds to use as beautiful cut flowers for bouquets. Ranunculus are a favorite for gardeners because they look like a mix between a rose and a peony. With proper care, they can bloom for many years, providing vibrant color and beauty to your garden or home.`},
{"heather": `Heather is a hardy evergreen shrub that is famous for its tiny and colorful bell-shaped flowers. It is native to Europe and Asia but is now grown in many parts of the world. This plant thrives in cool and moist climates where the summers are not too hot. It can tolerate very cold temperatures and even survives well in windy or coastal areas. Heather is most commonly grown in the highlands of Scotland and across northern European countries. The best time to plant heather is in the early spring or during the autumn months. It needs a sunny spot to grow well, although it can handle a little bit of light shade. This plant is very specific about its soil and strictly requires acidic ground to survive. The soil should be sandy, peaty, and very well-drained so that water does not sit around the roots. You should avoid planting heather in soil that contains a lot of lime or calcium. Because it grows in naturally poor soil, it does not need a lot of extra fertilizer. If you want to feed it, use a small amount of fertilizer designed for acid-loving plants in early spring. You should water young plants regularly until they are fully established in your garden. Once they are mature, they are quite tough and do not require much maintenance other than light pruning. Many gardeners love heather because it provides beautiful ground cover and stays green all year round. It is a wonderful choice for creating a natural and wild look in any landscape.`},
{"petunias": `Petunias are very popular garden flowers known for their wide variety of bright colors and patterns. They grow best in warm climates with plenty of sunshine and can tolerate moderate heat during the summer. These plants are most commonly grown in home gardens, hanging baskets, and decorative window boxes all over the world. You should plant petunias in the spring once the danger of frost has completely passed and the soil is warm. They need a location that receives at least six hours of direct sunlight every day to produce many flowers. The best soil for petunias is fertile, light, and must have very good drainage to prevent root issues. They do not like to stay in very wet or heavy clay soil for long periods of time. You should water them regularly, especially during hot and dry weeks, to keep the plants healthy. Because they grow and bloom so quickly, petunias need a lot of energy and regular feeding. It is best to use a balanced liquid fertilizer every two weeks throughout the entire growing season. For petunias in pots or hanging baskets, you may need to fertilize them once a week for the best results. A fertilizer high in phosphorus will help the plants produce a continuous supply of beautiful blossoms. You should also remove the old, faded flowers to encourage the plant to grow even more new buds. These flowers are a favorite for many people because they are easy to care for and bloom for many months. Adding petunias to your garden is a great way to enjoy vibrant colors from spring until the first frost of autumn.`},
{"amaryllis": `Amaryllis is a stunning tropical plant famous for its large and trumpet-shaped flowers. It naturally grows in warm and humid climates where there is no risk of freezing. In most parts of the world, it is grown indoors as a popular houseplant during the winter months. If you live in a very warm region, you can grow them outside in your garden all year round. The best time to plant the bulbs indoors is from late autumn to early winter. They need a bright and sunny spot, such as a windowsill that gets plenty of light. The soil should be rich in nutrients but also very light and well-drained. You should use a potting mix that contains some perlite or sand to keep the roots healthy. When planting, make sure that the top third of the bulb stays above the soil surface. You should water the plant sparingly at first until you see the green sprout starting to grow. Once the flower stem begins to rise, you can start watering more regularly to keep the soil moist. It is a good idea to use a balanced liquid fertilizer every two weeks during the growing period. Feeding the plant helps the bulb stay strong so it can bloom again in the following year. After the flowers fade, you should cut the stem but keep the leaves growing in the sun. These plants are loved because they produce spectacular blooms in bright red, pink, and white colors. With the right care, an amaryllis bulb can live for many years and bring beauty to your home.`},
{"yarrow": `Yarrow is a very hardy perennial plant known for its feathery leaves and flat clusters of small flowers. It is native to temperate regions of Europe, Asia, and North America where it grows naturally. This plant can tolerate a wide range of climates and is highly resistant to both cold and intense heat. It thrives best in full sun and loves open areas that get plenty of direct sunlight throughout the day. You can find yarrow growing almost everywhere, including wild meadows, roadsides, and home rock gardens. The best time to plant yarrow seeds or young plants is in the early spring after the frost is gone. It is highly adaptable and prefers average, well-drained soil that does not hold too much water. Yarrow actually grows better in poor or sandy soil and struggles in very rich, heavy clay ground. You do not need to water it often because it is very drought-tolerant once the roots develop. Because it naturally thrives in poor soils, yarrow generally does not require any extra fertilizer. Adding too much fertilizer can make the plant grow too tall and cause the stems to flop over. If your garden soil is completely bare of nutrients, a light layer of compost in the spring is more than enough. You should cut back the plant after the first flowers fade to encourage a second round of blooms. Many gardeners love yarrow because it attracts useful insects like bees and butterflies while keeping pests away. It is a beautiful, low-maintenance choice that brings bright yellow, pink, or white colors to any garden.`},
{"buttercups": `Buttercups are beautiful wild and garden flowers famous for their bright, glossy yellow petals. They belong to a large family of plants that mostly prefer cool and temperate climates. These plants can tolerate cold weather and frost very well, but they do not like extreme summer heat. You can find them growing naturally in meadows, fields, and near moist woodlands all over Europe and North America. They are also grown in home gardens around the world for their cheerful and sunny appearance. The best time to plant buttercup bulbs or seeds is in the autumn or early spring. They need a location that gets full sun or light shade to produce the best flowers. Buttercups love moist, rich soil that holds some water but still allows good drainage. They grow exceptionally well in heavy clay or loamy soil where other plants might struggle with moisture. You should water them regularly to keep the soil consistently damp, especially during dry spring weeks. Because they grow easily, wild buttercups do not need any extra fertilizer to thrive. For garden varieties, you can apply a balanced liquid fertilizer once a month in the spring. Feeding them helps the plants produce more blooms and stay strong throughout the flowering season. You should stop fertilizing once the flowers fade and the plant begins to go dormant. Many gardeners appreciate buttercups because they are very easy to grow and require very little maintenance. The bright yellow flowers with their shiny petals bring a touch of sunshine to any garden or natural area.`},
{"hellebores": `Hellebores are tough winter-flowering plants that people often call Christmas Roses or Lenten Roses. They can tolerate very cold climates and are strong enough to survive heavy snow and hard frost. These plants are native to Europe and Asia but they are grown in many shady gardens around the world. They grow best in cool areas and prefer deep shade or partial shade under large garden trees. It is best to plant them in the autumn or early spring when the weather is mild. Hellebores love rich, fertile soil that contains plenty of organic matter like compost. The ground should be moist but it must have good drainage so the roots do not sit in water. They prefer neutral or slightly alkaline soil and do not grow well in highly acidic dirt. You need to water the young plants regularly until they form a strong and deep root system. Mature hellebores are very tough and can survive dry summer periods without any problems. These plants do not need heavy chemical feeding to produce their beautiful nodding flowers. It is highly beneficial to put a fresh layer of organic compost around the base of the plant every autumn. You can also give them a light dose of balanced fertilizer in late winter just as new growth begins. Gardeners love hellebores because their tough, leathery leaves stay green and beautiful throughout the entire year. They are an amazing choice for adding bright white, pink, and purple colors to a quiet winter landscape.`},
{"columbines": `Columbines, also known as Aquilegia, are beautiful perennial flowers that look like little hats or birds. They grow best in cool and temperate climates, as they do not like extreme summer heat. These plants are native to the Northern Hemisphere and are very popular in North America, Europe, and parts of Asia. Gardeners love to grow them in mountain areas, woodlands, and cottage gardens. The best time to plant columbines is in the early spring or early autumn when the weather is mild. You can plant them from seeds directly into the garden or start them as small pot plants. They prefer rich, moist, and well-drained soil, but they can adapt to sandy or rocky soils too. The soil should be slightly acidic to neutral to keep them happy and healthy. Columbines like a spot with partial shade, especially in hot afternoons, though they can handle full sun in cooler regions. You should water them regularly to keep the soil moist, but make sure the roots do not sit in soggy mud. To help them grow strong, you can add some compost or organic matter to the soil before planting. For feeding, you can give them a balanced, water-soluble fertilizer once a month during the spring. Do not over-fertilize them, because too many nutrients can cause more green leaves than actual flowers. After they finish blooming in the summer, you can cut the flower stems down to the ground to help the plant save energy. They will easily drop their own seeds, so you will often find new baby columbines in your garden next year. The flowers come in many colors, including blue, purple, red, pink, and white, and they attract hummingbirds and butterflies to the garden. With proper care, columbines can bloom for many years and add a whimsical touch to any outdoor space.`},
{"morning"/*morning glories*/: `Morning Glories are beautiful climbing vines with colorful, trumpet-shaped flowers that open early in the morning. They love warm weather and thrive in hot, sunny climates, but they are sensitive to frost. These fast-growing plants are native to tropical areas of America and Asia, and they are very popular in backyard gardens all over the world. Gardeners usually grow them near fences, trellises, or walls so the vines have something to climb on. The best time to plant Morning Glories is in late spring, after all danger of winter frost has completely passed. You can plant the seeds directly into the garden soil once the ground becomes nice and warm. They prefer a sunny spot that gets at least six hours of direct sunlight every day to produce many blooms. These flowers love well-drained, average, or even poor soil, and they actually do not like earth that is too rich. If the soil has too many nutrients, the plant will grow lots of green leaves but very few flowers. You should water them regularly when they are young, but adult plants can tolerate dry soil quite well. To help the seeds germinate faster, you can soak them in water for a day before planting them in the ground. For feeding, you can give them a low-nitrogen, high-phosphorus fertilizer once a month during their growing season. Regular balanced fertilizers are not necessary and might stop them from producing their beautiful morning blossoms. Once they start growing, they need very little care and will bloom beautifully until the cold autumn weather arrives. These flowers come in many colors, including blue, purple, pink, red, and white, and they attract hummingbirds and butterflies to the garden. With proper care, Morning Glories can bloom for many years and add a vibrant splash of color to any outdoor space.`},
{"edelweiss": `Edelweiss is a famous mountain flower with beautiful, velvety white petals that look like stars. This tough plant loves cold climates and can easily survive strong winds, freezing temperatures, and winter frost. It is native to the high Alps and mountain regions of Europe, where it grows naturally on steep rocks. Today, gardeners grow it in rock gardens, alpine beds, and cold regions all over the world. The best time to plant edelweiss is in the early spring after the hard winter frost is gone. You can start the tiny seeds indoors during winter and move the small plants outside when it gets warmer. Edelweiss needs very poor, rocky, or sandy soil that drains water away quickly. It hates wet feet, so the soil must never stay soggy or heavy with clay. This flower loves full, bright sunlight and does not grow well in deep shade. You only need to water it a little bit, as it is very good at surviving dry weather. In fact, edelweiss does not need any fertilizer at all because rich food can actually kill the plant. It gets all its strength from the sun and clean, well-drained mountain-like soil. To protect the plant from rotting, you can put small pebbles or gravel around the base of the stem. During the winter, a good snow cover protects it, and it will grow back beautifully every spring. Edelweiss is a symbol of the Alps and is often associated with love, bravery, and purity. With proper care, this charming flower can bloom for many years, bringing a touch of alpine beauty to your garden.`},
{"clematis": `Clematis is a beautiful climbing plant known as the queen of climbers because of its stunning flowers. It grows best in temperate climates with cold winters and warm, gentle summers. This plant is very popular in Europe, North America, and parts of Asia, where people love to grow it over garden arches, fences, and trellises. The best time to plant clematis is in early spring or early autumn when the weather is mild and the soil is moist. When planting, it is very important to keep the roots in the shade and the green vines in the sun. Clematis prefers rich, deep, and well-drained soil that holds moisture but does not stay muddy. The soil should be neutral or slightly alkaline, so adding a little lime can help if your soil is acidic. You need to water the plant deeply and regularly, especially during hot and dry summer days. To keep the roots cool and damp, you can put a thick layer of mulch or flat stones around the base of the plant. For feeding, clematis is a hungry plant that needs plenty of nutrients to make big, beautiful blossoms. You should give it a balanced fertilizer in early spring when the new growth just starts to appear. You can feed it again with a high-potassium fertilizer, like tomato food, every two weeks during the spring growing season. Stop feeding the plant once it starts blooming so the flowers can last longer. With the right care and a sturdy support to climb on, clematis will bring wonderful colors to your garden for many years.`},
{"coreopsis": `Coreopsis is a cheerful perennial plant with bright yellow, daisy-like flowers that bring sunshine to any garden. This hardy plant loves warm weather and thrives in hot, sunny climates, but it can also survive cold winter temperatures. It is native to North America, where it is very popular in sunny flower beds, borders, and wild prairies. Gardeners love to grow it because it is tough, easy to care for, and blooms for a very long time. The best time to plant coreopsis is in the early spring after the danger of frost has passed, or in early autumn. You can easily start them from seeds directly in the ground or plant small potted starts from a nursery. Coreopsis prefers a spot that gets full, direct sunlight for at least six to eight hours every day. It loves well-drained, average, or even poor soil, and it actually dislikes soil that is too rich. If the ground has too many nutrients, the plant will grow floppy green leaves instead of beautiful blossoms. It can grow very well in dry, sandy, or rocky soils where other delicate flowers might struggle. You should water the young plants regularly to help them settle, but adult plants are very good at tolerating dry weather. For feeding, coreopsis does not need much fertilizer, so you only need to give it a light layer of compost in the spring. Adding too much chemical fertilizer can harm the plant and shorten its life. If you cut off the old, faded flowers during the summer, the plant will happily reward you with a second wave of bright blooms. These flowers come in many colors, including yellow, pink, red, and orange, and they attract butterflies and bees to the garden. With proper care, coreopsis can bloom for many years and add a vibrant splash of color to any outdoor space.`},
{"gentians": `Gentians are famous alpine plants known for their intense, beautiful blue flowers that look like small trumpets. These plants love cool and temperate climates, and they grow best in areas with cold winters and mild summers. They do not like hot, humid weather, so they struggle in tropical or very hot regions. Gentians are native to mountainous areas around the world, especially the European Alps, the Himalayas, and parts of North America. Gardeners love to grow them in rock gardens, alpine beds, and cool hillside gardens. The best time to plant gentians is in the early spring or early autumn when the weather is gentle and cool. You can plant them from seeds or move small potted plants into the garden soil carefully. They prefer rich, moist, but very well-drained soil that mimics their natural mountain home. The soil should be slightly acidic to neutral, and it must never become heavy with clay or stay soggy. They love a spot with bright morning sunlight but need partial shade during the hot afternoon hours. You should water them regularly to keep the soil consistently damp, because they hate completely dry ground. For feeding, gentians do not need strong chemical fertilizers, as too much food can easily damage them. Instead, you can give them a thin layer of organic compost or a very weak, diluted liquid fertilizer once in the early spring. Removing weeds around them is important because these slow-growing plants do not like to fight for space. With a little patience and the right cool conditions, gentians will reward you with the most striking blue color in your garden.`},
{"tuberoses": `Tuberoses are beautiful, tall plants famous for their white flowers and incredibly sweet, strong perfume. They love warm weather and thrive best in hot, tropical, or subtropical climates. These plants are native to Mexico, and they are widely grown in warm regions like India, southern Europe, and the southern parts of North America. In colder places, gardeners grow them in pots so they can move them indoors before winter arrives. The best time to plant tuberoses is in late spring when the soil becomes warm and all danger of frost is gone. You plant them from bulb-like structures called rhizomes, placing them about two inches deep in the ground. They need a very sunny spot that receives full, direct sunlight for at least six to eight hours every day. Tuberoses prefer rich, fertile, and well-drained soil that can hold moisture without becoming soggy or muddy. To give them a good start, you can mix plenty of organic compost or aged manure into the garden bed before planting. You should water the plants deeply and regularly during the summer to keep the soil consistently moist. For feeding, tuberoses are very hungry plants that need lots of nutrients to produce their heavy, fragrant blossoms. You should give them a balanced, slow-release fertilizer or a high-phosphorus food once a month during the growing season. Stop feeding them in late summer when the blooming finishes and the plant prepares for its rest. If you live in a cold area, you must dig up the rhizomes in autumn and store them in a dry, warm place until next spring. These flowers are a favorite for gardeners who love fragrant blooms, and with proper care, tuberoses can bloom for many years, filling the air with their delightful scent.`},
{"wild"/*wild roses*/: `Wild roses are tough, natural shrubs that are famous for their simple, fragrant flowers and bright red autumn berries. They can tolerate a wide range of climates, easily surviving freezing winter cold and hot summer days. These hardy plants are native to the Northern Hemisphere and grow widely across North America, Europe, and Asia. You can find them growing naturally along country roads, in open fields, and in home gardens. The best time to plant wild roses is in the early spring or late autumn when the plant is resting and the weather is mild. You can plant bare-root bushes or small potted plants directly into your garden soil. They prefer a spot that gets full, direct sunlight for at least six hours every day to produce the best blossoms. Wild roses like well-drained, average soil, but they are very adaptable and can grow in sandy, rocky, or clay soils too. Unlike delicate garden roses, they do not need highly rich earth and can thrive where other plants struggle. You should water young plants regularly during their first year, but adult bushes become very good at tolerating dry weather. For feeding, wild roses do not need heavy chemical fertilizers, as too many nutrients can actually make them weak. Instead, you can give them a layer of organic compost or well-rotted manure around the base in early spring. This single spring feeding gives them enough energy to grow strong stems and beautiful, healthy flowers for the whole season. They are very easy to look after, require minimal pruning, and will happily grow in your garden for many decades. The simple, five-petaled flowers come in many colors, including pink, white, and yellow, and they attract bees and butterflies to the garden. With proper care, wild roses can bloom for many years, adding natural beauty and charm to any outdoor space.`}
]